Debra LaFave, a newly married 24-year old Tampa area teacher arrested in June 2004 was charged with lewd and lascivious battery, involving four encounters in two different counties with a 14-year old student, evidence including photos and tapes.
Defense Attorney John Fitzgibbons offered a plea of not guilty by insanity, bipolar disorder, but media attention caused the boy's mother to accept an agreement with Judge Wayne Timmerman of Hillsborough County for penalties but no imprisonment.
Judge Hale Stancil in Marion County refused agreement in December 2005.
Ric Ridgeway of the State Attorney's Office said new plea deal would be proposed.
